    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense, but i'm trying to get a more specific sense of the real-world consequences. i've been reading some stuff online that says these wage hikes basically force small shops to close or cut staff, while others say it's actually good for the local economy in the long run. in your experience with business data, is one of those views more grounded in reality than the other? like, are the arguments for raising it just more about the \"feeling\" of fairness, or is there actual economic evidence that it works for small towns?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
